            <div class="sl-card-title">Unburden Exiled Parts</div>
            <div class="sl-card-text">Follow the safe, structured IFS process for accessing the most wounded, traumatized parts of yourself and offering them the healing they've been longing for.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- FEATURES -->
  <div class="sl-section">
    <div class="sl-section-inner">
      <div class="sl-label">Why This Book</div>
      <h2 class="sl-title">A Genuinely Different Healing Path</h2>
      <div class="sl-features-grid">
        <div class="sl-feature-item">
          <div class="sl-check">✓</div>
          <div>
            <div class="sl-feature-text">C-PTSD Specific</div>
            <div class="sl-feature-sub">Written specifically for survivors of developmental trauma, emotional neglect, domestic abuse, and other prolonged adverse experiences.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sl-feature-item">
          <div class="sl-check">✓</div>
          <div>
            <div class="sl-feature-text">Beyond Talk Therapy</div>
            <div class="sl-feature-sub">IFS bypasses the thinking brain to reach deeper emotional truths, making it effective even when years of conventional therapy haven't been enough.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sl-feature-item">
          <div class="sl-check">✓</div>
          <div>
            <div class="sl-feature-text">Restores the Self</div>
            <div class="sl-feature-sub">Rebuilds a stable, compassionate sense of "Self" as the leader of your inner world—the foundation for lasting recovery from complex trauma.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sl-feature-item">
          <div class="sl-check">✓</div>
          <div>
            <div class="sl-feature-text">No Re-Traumatization</div>
            <div class="sl-feature-sub">The IFS model is inherently gentle. You never have to relive traumatic memories in graphic detail for deep healing to occur.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- REVIEWS -->
  <div class="sl-section" style="background: var(--surface);">
    <div class="sl-section-inner">
      <div style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 48px;">
        <div class="sl-label">Verified Reviews</div>
        <h2 class="sl-title">What Readers Are Saying</h2>
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;gap:12px;margin-top:16px;">
          <span style="color:#f6ad55;font-size:1.5rem;">★★★★★</span>
          <span style="font-size:1.1rem;font-weight:800;color:var(--text-primary);">4.9 out of 5</span>
          <span style="font-size:0.9rem;color:var(--text-secondary);">· Verified readers</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="sl-reviews-grid">

        <div class="sl-review-card">
          <div class="sl-review-stars">★★★★★</div>
          <div class="sl-review-title">Finally something that works for C-PTSD</div>
          <div class="sl-review-meta">Verified Reader &nbsp;·&nbsp; <span class="sl-verified">✓ Verified Purchase</span></div>
          <div class="sl-review-text">I spent years in CBT and DBT therapy and while helpful, something was always missing. This book and the IFS model reached the parts of my trauma that nothing else could touch.</div>
          <div class="sl-review-helpful">👍 Helpful</div>
        </div>

        <div class="sl-review-card">
          <div class="sl-review-stars">★★★★★</div>
          <div class="sl-review-title">The most compassionate trauma book I've read</div>
          <div class="sl-review-meta">Verified Reader &nbsp;·&nbsp; <span class="sl-verified">✓ Verified Purchase</span></div>
          <div class="sl-review-text">The tone of this book made me feel completely safe. There is zero shame, zero blame. It explains why I am the way I am and shows me how to heal without reliving the worst moments.</div>
          <div class="sl-review-helpful">👍 Helpful</div>
        </div>

        <div class="sl-review-card">
          <div class="sl-review-stars">★★★★★</div>
          <div class="sl-review-title">My dissociation finally makes sense</div>
          <div class="sl-review-meta">Verified Reader &nbsp;·&nbsp; <span class="sl-verified">✓ Verified Purchase</span></div>
          <div class="sl-review-text">Understanding my dissociation as a protective part rather than a flaw completely changed my relationship with it. I can now work with it instead of fighting it.</div>
          <div class="sl-review-helpful">👍 Helpful</div>
        </div>

        <div class="sl-review-card">
          <div class="sl-review-stars">★★★★★</div>
          <div class="sl-review-title">Recommended by my trauma therapist</div>
          <div class="sl-review-meta">Verified Reader &nbsp;·&nbsp; <span class="sl-verified">✓ Verified Purchase</span></div>
          <div class="sl-review-text">My therapist handed me this book and said it was the best companion guide available for IFS-based trauma work. She was absolutely right. Transformative reading.</div>
          <div class="sl-review-helpful">👍 Helpful</div>
        </div>

        <div class="sl-review-card">
          <div class="sl-review-stars">★★★★★</div>
          <div class="sl-review-title">Healing without re-traumatization</div>
          <div class="sl-review-meta">Verified Reader &nbsp;·&nbsp; <span class="sl-verified">✓ Verified Purchase</span></div>
          <div class="sl-review-text">So many trauma approaches felt unsafe to me because they asked me to relive awful memories. This book respects your system's pace and never forces anything. It felt like true healing.</div>
          <div class="sl-review-helpful">👍 Helpful</div>
        </div>

        <div class="sl-review-card">
          <div class="sl-review-stars">★★★★★</div>
          <div class="sl-review-title">I recognized myself on every page</div>
          <div class="sl-review-meta">Verified Reader &nbsp;·&nbsp; <span class="sl-verified">✓ Verified Purchase</span></div>
